author: rlubke
msg: - merged positivePrint<TYPE>(MAX|MIN)Boundry tests into their respective
positivePrint<type> tests.  The spec doesn't explicitly state that this
functionality needs to be tested, but it doesn't hurt to make sure
that the positivePrint<TYPE> tests can handle the MAX_VALUE and MIN_VALUES
of a particular integer or floating point type.

author: rlubke
msg: Enhanced test to do more than just call out.flush().
- get the buffer size of the page (out.getBufferSize())
- write data to the buffer and flush
- validate that the buffer is clean by checking
the buffer size from the first step against a call
to out.getRemaining().  The values should be equal.
